om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Oh McKinsey</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/25653399.264655/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNz=
LXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMS0yMzA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB10b95ef0" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Come on<=
/a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Securities and Exchang=
e Commission today charged Puneet Dikshit, a partner at a global management=
 consulting firm, with illegally trading in advance of a corporate acquisit=
ion by one of the firm=E2=80=99s clients in September.</p><p style=3D"margi=
n: 16px 0;">The SEC=E2=80=99s complaint, filed in federal district court in=
 Manhattan, alleges that in the course of providing consulting services, Di=
kshit learned highly confidential information concerning The Goldman Sachs =
Group Inc.=E2=80=99s impending acquisition of the consumer loan fintech pla=
tform GreenSky Inc. =C2=A0According to the SEC=E2=80=99s complaint, in the =
days leading up to the acquisition announcement on Sept. 15, 2021, Dikshit =
used this information to purchase out-of-the-money GreenSky call options th=
at were set to expire just days after the announcement. =C2=A0The SEC=E2=80=
=99s complaint further alleges that Dikshit violated his firm=E2=80=99s pol=
icies by failing to pre-clear these options purchases, which he sold on the=
 morning of the acquisition announcement for illicit profits totaling over =
$450,000.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWe allege that Dikshit b=
reached duties to his employer and his client by misusing their confidentia=
l information for his own financial gain,=E2=80=9D said Joseph G. Sansone, =
Chief of the SEC Enforcement Division=E2=80=99s Market Abuse Unit. =C2=A0=
=E2=80=9CThanks to our trading analysis tools, we were able to move swiftly=
 to hold him accountable for his actions and protect the fairness of our se=
curities markets.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">He =
also faces <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2565339=
9.264655/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuanVzdGljZS5nb3YvdXNhby1zZG55L3ByL21hbmFnZW1lbnQtY2=
9uc3VsdGluZy1maXJtLXBhcnRuZXItY2hhcmdlZC1pbnNpZGVyLXRyYWRpbmctc2NoZW1l/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0c18f487" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">criminal charges</a>. The =E2=80=9Cg=
lobal management consulting firm=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/25653399.264655/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9=
uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTEtMTAvZ29sZG1hbi1jb25zdWx0YW50LWlsbGVnYWxseS10cm=
FkZWQtb24tZ3JlZW5za3ktZGVhbC1zZWMtc2F5cz9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTEwMjFfTU9ORVlTVFVGR=
iZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMTExMTAm=
dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB65b289be" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
is of course</a> McKinsey &amp; Co., which Goldman hired to help with due d=
iligence and then integration for=C2=A0its acquisition of GreenSky. Dikshit=
 was a partner =E2=80=94=C2=A0a partner! =E2=80=94=C2=A0on the assignment, =
and, once Goldman formally hired McKinsey to help with the integration =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0making clear that a deal was imminent =E2=80=94=C2=A0he alleged=
ly <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25653399.264655=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9saXRpZ2F0aW9uL2NvbXBsYWludHMvMjAyMS9jb21wLXByMj=
AyMS0yMzAucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfcde6790" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" it=
emscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">did this</a>:</p>=
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At 3:41 p.m. on September 13, usin=
g an IP address associated with Consulting Firm, Dikshit purchased 212 GSKY=
 call option contracts with a $10 strike price and a September 17 expiratio=
n date at a cost of approximately $2,100. These highly speculative call opt=
ion contracts=C2=A0would expire worthless if by September 17 the price of G=
SKY did not increase approximately 13% from its September 13 closing price =
of $8.85 per share to the strike price of $10 per share.</p></blockquote><p=
 style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The next day, Sept. 14,=C2=A0Goldman=E2=80=99s b=
oard approved the transaction and Dikshit allegedly <em>sold=C2=A0</em>some=
 longer-dated GreenSky call options to raise cash to buy thousands=C2=A0mor=
e Sept. 17 $10-strike options for $21,000. Gotta maximize leverage, you kno=
w? The next day, Sept. 15, Goldman announced the deal, GreenSky closed up 5=
3% at $11.90, and, allegedly:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A=
fter the pre-market announcement, between 9:34 a.m. and 9:35 a.m., Dikshit,=
 using an IP address associated with Consulting Firm, placed orders to liqu=
idate the 2,481 GSKY call option contracts he had purchased in his account =
on September 13 and 14, which he had acquired at=C2=A0a cost of approximate=
ly $23,100. Those orders were executed between 9:35 a.m. and 9:42 a.m. for =
proceeds of $449,128.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Al=
so <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25653399.264655=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTEtMTAvZ29sZG=
1hbi1jb25zdWx0YW50LWlsbGVnYWxseS10cmFkZWQtb24tZ3JlZW5za3ktZGVhbC1zZWMtc2F5c=
z9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTEwMjFfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9=
bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMTExMTAmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cC65b289be" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> not ideal</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The consultant made his trades using an account in his=
 name and one in his spouse=E2=80=99s name, according to the SEC. Evidence =
of Dikshit=E2=80=99s insider trading was found on his work computer, prosec=
utors said. On the day before the GreenSky deal was announced, Dikshit used=
 Google to search: =E2=80=9Cwhat happens to options when company is acquire=
d=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cgreensky market cap.=E2=80=9D He also used it to ch=
eck his broker=E2=80=99s web page for information about $10 GreenSky call o=
ptions, they said.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Three weeks later, after=
 news of suspicious trading in GreenSky options, Dikshit used his McKinsey =
computer to run searches about Rajat Gupta=E2=80=99s insider trading convic=
tion.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If I were Goldman I=E2=
=80=99d be mad! Not because of the =E2=80=9Cmisusing their confidential inf=
ormation=E2=80=9D stuff; that=E2=80=99s embarrassing but it=E2=80=99s not l=
ike Dikshit=E2=80=99s alleged trading=C2=A0drove up the price Goldman had t=
o pay for GreenSky or anything. Just because of the operational incompetenc=
e! This is the guy you hired to advise you on your integration of a financi=
al services firm and he=E2=80=99s (allegedly) out there=C2=A0<em>buying sho=
rt-dated out-of-the-money call options on the target of a merger he=E2=80=
=99s working=C2=A0on</em>? In his own name? From his work computer? Come on=
! This is the most basic <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com=
/click/25653399.264655/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGlj=
bGVzLzIwMTgtMDgtMTIvdGhlLTEwLWxhd3Mtb2YtaW5zaWRlci10cmFkaW5nP2NtcGlkPUJCRDE=
xMTAyMV9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJn=
V0bV90ZXJtPTIxMTExMCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a2=
3cBfe67da81" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blan=
k" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; back=
ground-color: #ccc;">rule of insider trading</a>, that you don=E2=80=99t do=
 that. This is not legal advice but it is =E2=80=A6=C2=A0it's just =E2=80=
=A6=C2=A0it=E2=80=99s best practices, you know? If you=E2=80=99re a managem=
ent consultant you should be a bit more strategic.</p><table class=3D"livei=
ntent-sponsored-content" width=3D"auto" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0"=
>
