lon Musk, launched his now infamous Twitter poll.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16=
px 0;">Kimbal, a Tesla board member, sold 88,500 Tesla shares on Nov. 5, ac=
cording to a=C2=A0filing=C2=A0that day after the market close. He sold the =
stake at an average price of $1,229.91 per share via JPMorgan, the filing s=
ays. That amounts to about $109 million. The shares sold represented about =
15% of Kimbal=E2=80=99s equity stake, excluding options.</p></blockquote><p=
 style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I suppose the specific questions would be (1) do=
 you think that, when Kimbal sold his stock, he knew that Elon was going to=
 tweet his poll the next day, and (2) if he did know, would that be bad? Be=
 careful with the second one! For one thing, it is not clear that the poll =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0a binary choice of =E2=80=9Csell=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Cdon=E2=
=80=99t sell=E2=80=9D tweeted out to millions of random people on Twitter =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0was material nonpublic information. Arguably the information=
 content of the poll is =E2=80=9CElon Musk will sell stock or he won=E2=80=
=99t,=E2=80=9D which is sort of always true. (Arguably the information cont=
ent is =E2=80=9CElon Musk is much more likely to sell stock than he was bef=
ore tweeting this poll,=E2=80=9D because you assumed he=E2=80=99s not a big=
 seller and/or because you know Twitter users will always choose the more c=
haotic option =E2=80=94=C2=A0but, as we discussed on Monday, Musk has=C2=A0=
<em>already said publicly that he=E2=80=99s going to sell a big block of st=
ock by the end of the year</em>.)</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For anoth=
er thing, even if Elon=E2=80=99s poll was material nonpublic information, i=
sn=E2=80=99t it=C2=A0<em>his=C2=A0</em>material nonpublic information? Can=
=E2=80=99t he sell stock when he wants, or do stunts around his stock sales=
 if he wants, and=C2=A0<em>tell whoever he wants about his plans?=C2=A0</em=
>This is complicated by the fact that he=E2=80=99s the chief executive offi=
cer and controlling shareholder of Tesla (and Kimbal is a board member),[1]=
 but they are both selling in their personal capacity, and=C2=A0<em>in gene=
